Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Core, seed, and cut @poblano pepper{2} into small squares. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{4}, separating greens and whites. Zest @lime{2}, then cut each into quarters.

Prick @sweet potatoes{4} all over with a #fork{}. Place on a #plate{}. Microwave on high until tender, ~{8-12%minutes}.

> A fork should easily glide into the center of the potatoes. If not tender, continue to microwave in 1 minute increments.

Set aside to cool.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, lime zest, 2 tablespoons water, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of @salt{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{20%ounce}, garlic, poblanos, scallion whites, @Southwest spice blend{2%tablespoon}, salt, @pepper{}, and @chipotle powder{1/2%tsp}. Cook, tossing, until pork is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> Add more chipotle if you like it spicy.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{2} and 1/2 cup water, stirring until thoroughly combined.

Halve sweet potatoes lengthwise; fluff insides with a fork. Top each half with 1/2 tablespoon @butter{4%tablespoon}; sprinkle with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide sweet potatoes between plates and top with pork mixture. Evenly sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1%cup} and drizzle with crema. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with @hot sauce{2%teaspoon} and remaining lime quarters on the side.